{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "Being lied to has a corrosive, life-changing impact.", "abstract": "Op-Ed article by psychiatrist Anna Fels describes how those who experience great betrayals at the hands of spouses or family members have a difficult time dealing with the revelation; notes that those who are the betrayers tend to have an easier time; maintains that therapy can help those who have been lied to construct a narrative that serves as an internal structure for conducting their lives from that point on.", "section_name": "Opinion", "print_page": "9", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"firstname": "Anna", "role": "reported", "lastname": "FELS", "rank": 1, "organization": ""}], "original": "By ANNA FELS", "contributor": ""}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2013/10/06/opinion/sunday/great-betrayals.html", "lead_paragraph": "Being lied to has a corrosive, life-changing impact.", "headline": {"main": "Great Betrayals", "print_headline": "Great Betrayals", "content_kicker": "Opinion", "kicker": "Opinion"}, "_id": "52505ab238f0d819897407b6", "word_count": "1213", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2013/10/06/sunday-review/06Betrayalsub/06Betrayalsub-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2013/10/06/sunday-review/06Betrayalsub/06Betrayalsub-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 429, "url": "images/2013/10/06/sunday-review/06Betrayalsub/06Betrayalsub-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2013/10/06/sunday-review/06Betrayalsub/06Betrayalsub-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "429"}, "subtype": "xlarge", "width": 600, "type": "image"}, {"height": 75, "url": "images/2013/10/06/sunday-review/06Betrayalsub/06Betrayalsub-thumbStandard.jpg", "legacy": {"thumbnail": "images/2013/10/06/sunday-review/06Betrayalsub/06Betrayalsub-thumbStandard.jpg", "thumbnailwidth": "75", "thumbnailheight": "75"}, "subtype": "thumbnail", "